description:
Inside this issue:

Justice League - Part 4

The team is almost complete! Aquaman has arrived on shore to help the Justice League in their fight against the monstrous creatures of Apokolips! But there's still one hero left to join their ranks - it's time for Cyborg to step up! The stakes are raised when the greatest evil in the DC Universe is revealed!

Action Comics: Superman And The Men of Steel - Part 4

The threat of an alien invasion looms large over Metropolis, and the city has turned on it's super saviour! Meanwhile, rejected by Louis Lane, soldier John Corben volunteers himself for the Steel Soldier programme, but a corruption in the programming reveals that the invasion has already begun!

Green Lantern: Sinestro - Part 4

Having taken a reluctant Hal Jordan under his wing, recently reinstated Green Lantern Sinestro is on a mission to save his homeland from his former Corps of Yellow Lanterns! But with Jordan seemingly dead from disintegration, can Sinestro take on his old team mates alone?
name: Justice League Part Four

description: In 1982, conflict erupts between Great Britain and Argentina. Argentina decides to seize the Falkland Islands, occupied by the United Kingdom since the beginning of the 19th century. On April 2, an island landing of Argentine forces succeeds, taking the government of Margaret Thatcher by surprise. Argentina asserts its sovereignty over the Islands. While hoping for a diplomatic solution, No. 10 Downing Street prepares a large-scale operation to regain control of the Falkland Islands. Along with the use of traditional combat techniques, these operations also provide an extraordinary test of modern electronic weaponry.
name: The Falkland Wars

description: Peter Parker's life has always been one of constant turmoil, with the lives and loves that are part of it at constant risk due to the fated meeting with a radioactive spider that spawned his heroic destiny. But as readers of CIVIL WAR and 'Back in Black' know, it is now that Peter struggles through perhaps his darkest days. MARVEL SPOTLIGHT flips the calendar on 'One More Day,' the flashpoint for Spider-Man's crisis of hope and faith, and looks ahead to the 'Brand New Day' that awaits both Spider-Man and his loyal readers. With insider access to the event that will transform everything you think you know about Peter Parker, you do NOT want to miss this issue of SPOTLIGHT!
name: Marvel Spotlight: Spider-Man

volume.name: Marvel Spotlight: Spider-Man - One More Day/Brand New Day
